artifacts.action_items:
[
  {
    "task": "Provide a note on reserves for the last four years",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Lynne Neagle AM: You did say that you would give the committee a note on reserves for the last four years, so we'd be grateful if we could receive that."
  },
  {
    "task": "Review and refresh the toolkit for governors",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Dr David Blaney: Whether that toolkit needs a refresh—I’m sure it probably does, it’s been there for a while now—."
  },
  {
    "task": "Conduct a review of governance in Wales",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Dr David Blaney: We’ll be alongside that. We’ll be supporting that. But, actually, it’s important that they own it."
  },
  {
    "task": "Maintain the attractiveness of Welsh universities to students",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: And, just to add, I think the key bit of that is maintaining the attractiveness of Welsh universities to students, because a large proportion are coming not from just Wales, but from England and internationally—so, that’s a key part—"
  },
  {
    "task": "Increase openness and transparency around the use of fee income",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: The reporting of the income and expenditure is largely provided, probably more so in narrative form in the accounts and the financial statements and annual reports of institutions."
  },
  {
    "task": "Support and fund growth in part-time provision",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: We've allocated £26.5 million in 2019-20 to support part-time provision, and we have been able in 2019-20 to fund some growth."
  },
  {
    "task": "Maintain QR funding in real terms",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Dr David Blaney: The reason the sum hasn't increased is because we haven't had enough money to be able to increase it and still meet the obligations we have to other bits of the HE system."
  },
  {
    "task": "Place funding back into the system for innovation",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "2020-21",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: One aspect that we do intend to fund—and this is from Diamond, as well as Reid—is to place funding back into the system for innovation."
  },
  {
    "task": "Strengthen the relationship with the UK machinery",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "none",
    "evidence": "Dr David Blaney: And that is actually paying dividends; we are strengthening our relationship with the UK machinery, which is essential if we're to understand where they're heading and what their funding bids are all about, and even to be able to influence those."
  },
  {
    "task": "Provide £15 million in innovation funding",
    "owner": "HEFCW",
    "deadline": "2020-21",
    "evidence": "Bethan Owen: That’s funding that we had to take out when the new fee system came in. That is part of promoting the innovation, and part of the research portfolio as well."
  }
]

